\,\,\frac{x^2}{cy+bz}=\frac{y^2}{az+cx}=\frac{z^2}{bx+ay}=1,
\frac{a}{a+x}+\frac{b}{b+y}+\frac{c}{c+z}=1
x^2=cy+bz\iff ax+cy+bz=x^2+ax=x(x+a)
\implies\frac1{a+x}=\frac x{ax+cy+bz}\implies \frac  a{a+x}=\frac{ax}{ax+cy+bz}
x=y=1, z=-1
 a= \frac 12,b= \frac 12,c= \frac 32.  
 -a+c=1, \\b+a=1,\\ -b+c=1. 
 {\frac {a}{a+x}}+{\frac {b}{b+y}}+{\frac {c}{c+z}}={\frac {a}{a+1}}+{\frac {b}{b+1}}+{\frac {c}{c-1}}=\frac{11}{3}\neq 1. 
